            "sufficient human contribution, cannot be",
            "copyrighted in the United States.",
            "The Supreme Court\u2019s decision not to",
            "review the case effectively upholds the",
            "existing legal framework regarding",
            "AI-generated art and copyright.",
            "The Supreme Court\u2019s inaction leaves the",
            "lower court rulings in place,",
            "establishing a clear precedent.",
            "The courts have consistently maintained",
            "that human involvement is essential for",
            "a work to be protected by copyright.",
            "The ruling clarifies that simply using",
            "an AI tool does not automatically grant",
            "copyright to the resulting work.",
            "This decision impacts the growing field",
            "of AI art and its legal status."
          ]
        }
